 Title:
 Assistant Professor (Engineering)
 Deadline to Apply:
 08/16/2021
 Application Deadline:
 or until filled
 Job Category:
 Faculty
 College:
 College of Engineering-SIUC
 Position Summary:
 The School of Applied Engineering and Technology invites applications for the position of Assistant Professor. This is a continuing, tenure track position starting January 1, 2022. 
 The College houses six schools: Applied Engineering and Technology; Computing; Electrical, Computer & Biomedical Engineering; Civil, Environmental & Infrastructure Engineering; Mathematical and Statistical Sciences; Mechanical, Aerospace & Materials Engineering. The breadth of programs offered in the college provides a rich environment for interdisciplinary collaborative research. We welcome applicants with backgrounds including, but not limited to, Industrial, Electrical, Systems or Quality Engineering, Operations Research or Artificial Intelligence. 
 
 Duties and Responsibilities:
 The successful candidate will teach courses at the undergraduate and graduate level, engage in scholarly research, develop an externally funded research program and provide School/University Service appropriate to academic rank. 
 
 Minimum Qualifications:
 Applicants must possess a doctoral degree in a related engineering or science discipline. ABD applicants may be considered if all requirements for the doctoral degree are completed prior to commencement of employment in accordance with University policy. https://policies.siu.edu/personnel-policies/chapter2/ch2 -faps/conting.php 
 Preferred Qualifications:
 Candidates who have experience working with a diverse range of faculty, staff, and students and who can contribute to the climate of inclusivity are encouraged to identify their experiences in these areas in their cover letter. 
 Special Instructions for Applicants:  A cover letter is required and should be uploaded to your application along with a curriculum vitae, transcripts, and statements of teaching and research interests (1-2 pages for each, upload as document type "other"). 
 If selected for interview, references (please list 3 on the application) will be sent an email to upload a letter of reference. Please advise your references that the email will come from noreply@hiretouch.com. 
 General Information - College/Department:
 Southern Illinois University Carbondale is a Carnegie Doctoral Research University. SIU is located in the forested areas of Shawnee Hills, 100 miles southeast of St. Louis, MO. The university is known for its efforts in improving opportunity, inclusivity, sustainability and the ecological beauty of the campus and surrounding community. Information about the School of Applied Engineering and Technology can be found at: https://engineering.siu.edu/tech/ More information about SIU and its surrounding community can be found at: https://siu.edu/about-siu/.
 Required Documents:
 Cover Letter, Curriculum Vitae, Other, Transcripts
 Contact:
